on slowly. We conclude that:\n1) J-PLUS filters can be used to measure quenching timescales in nearby green\nvalley galaxies; and 2) the resulting star formation quenching time-scales are\nlonger for barred green valley galaxies. Considering that the presence of a bar\nindicates that more violent processes (e.g., major mergers) are absent in host\ngalaxies, we conclude that the presence of a bar can be used as a morphological\nsignature for slow star formation quenching.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Jul 2019 18:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-25"}
