med in the context of the philosophy of the Upanishads, according to which\nwe (as Schr\\\"odinger put it) \"are all really only various aspects of the One.\"\nThere is no world that exists out of relation to consciousness, but there are\ndifferent poises of consciousness. In particular, there is a poise of\nconsciousness peculiar to the human species at this point in time, and there\nare poises of consciousness that are yet to evolve (and that may be essential\nto averting the calamities towards which humanity appears to be heading).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 26 Jul 2019 07:15:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 Nov 2019 07:26:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-02"}
